  "market_context": "Weekly profile where Friday prior formed a reversal candle (candle-to-closure) paired with SMT, enabling Monday long bias; Monday–Wednesday expanded higher without forming a significant new low inside the weekly range, setting up Thursday as potential counter day.",
  "key_observation": "Thursday countered the three-day expansion with an SMT divergence and hourly change in state of delivery (CISD) at the previous day high, confirming a reversal and setting up Friday for continuation lower toward weekly open.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified Friday’s reversal candle (candle-to-closure) paired with SMT, establishing bullish bias for Monday.",
    "Step 2: Observed Monday–Tuesday–Wednesday all expanding higher without forming a significant new low inside the weekly range.",
    "Step 3: Noted the absence of a meaningful low inside the weekly range, signaling potential for a Thursday counter move.",
    "Step 4: Switched to hourly timeframe to confirm SMT at previous day high and change in state of delivery (CISD) on the wick, validating the reversal.",
    "Step 5: Anticipated Friday as continuation day lower targeting weekly open and current week low/failure swings."
  ],
  "outcome": "Friday delivered a strong expansion lower into the weekly open, confirming the Thursday counter profile.",
  "lessons": "A multi-day expansion without a counter low creates vulnerability to a Thursday counter; SMT + CISD on hourly confirms the reversal, and Friday continuation to weekly open validates the weekly profile structure.",
